# ClaudeRabbit CLI — configuration
#
# ClaudeRabbit is a free, no-login, public tool: the Supabase URL and the
# Supabase PUBLISHABLE key are not secrets (they are the exact two values the
# public web app ships in its own client bundle — see the root .env.example
# and docs/INFRASTRUCTURE.md §3/§7). This CLI ships with them as built-in
# defaults so it works out of the box with zero configuration.
#
# Only set these if you are pointing the CLI at a different ClaudeRabbit
# deployment (e.g. a fork, a staging project, or a future production URL).

# Supabase project URL for the ClaudeRabbit deployment to call.
# CLAUDE_RABBIT_SUPABASE_URL=https://mjvlczaytkhvsolnhhkz.supabase.co

# Supabase PUBLISHABLE key (sb_publishable_...) — safe to ship client-side,
# this is the same key the ClaudeRabbit web app uses for anonymous scans.
# CLAUDE_RABBIT_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=sb_publishable_HAPgnT9M5Sr166Se8Nx0yg_qxzn-08B

# Public site origin used to build the "full report" links printed by the CLI.
# Defaults to the local dev origin below; override once a production domain is live.
# CLAUDE_RABBIT_SITE_URL=http://localhost:2311

# Request timeout for a fresh (uncached) scan, in milliseconds. A fresh scan
# streams NDJSON stage events and can take tens of seconds; this bounds how
# long the command will block waiting for the final result.
# CLAUDE_RABBIT_SCAN_TIMEOUT_MS=120000
